<DOC><DOCNO> AP900222-0131 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-22-90 1614EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-BRF--UMassPresident     02-22 0158</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--UMass President,0162</SECOND><HEAD>UMass Chancellor to Fill President's Post</HEAD><DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The chancellor of the University of Massachusettsat Amherst will assume the additional role of university presidentafter David C. Knapp steps down in March, the school announcedThursday.   As president, Joseph Duffey will oversee fiscal operations atthe university's three campuses at Amherst, Boston and Worchester.Knapp, 62, announced Thursday that he will leave on March 16 afteralmost 12 years on the job.   At a board of trustees meeting, Duffey, 57, said he was takingthe job with some reluctance because the university's financialstate will require layoffs.   ``Who would look forward to eliminating the jobs of hard-workingmen and women?'' he asked.   Duffey, chancellor for nearly eight years, intends to bring muchof the president's operation to the Amherst campus from Boston, theuniversity said.   Amherst is the largest campus in the UMass system, which has atotal enrollment of about 40,000.</TEXT></DOC>